caption: Potbelly sandwiches fall in line with your subway and other quick sandwich shops. I particularly like their chicken salad with bacon and provolone cheese. There toppings are kinda limited.

They don't overdo it with the toppings to where they are falling out of the bun. Their mac n cheese is the bomb. It's  very creamy. I also love their hot peppers.

caption: After breakfast at Potbelly, we left hungry and longing for a better taste.

(2/16/16) THIS LOCATION (1275 1ST ST NE) IS THE WORST!  I HIGHLY RECOMMEND TRAINING, BETTER QUALITY OF FOOD AND A WELCOMING STAFF!  THE STAFF ACTS ANNOYED THAT THE CLIENT ENTERS THE STORE, NOT TO MENTION, MAKE AN ORDER.  THE CURRENT STAFF DEFINITELY DO NOT HAVE THE PROPER ETIQUETTE QUALIFIED FOR A CUSTOMER SERVICE ENVIRONMENT!  THE FOOD: TOMATOES SOGGY, LETTUCE WARPED, CHICKEN SALAD THE WORST I'VE EVER EXPERIENCED AT A POTBELLY... I CAN KEEP GOING.  MANAGEMENT NEEDS TO TAKE A LONG HARD LOOK AT STAFF, AND PERHAPS SELF!  AS SERVICE, ATTITUDE, FOOD, DELIVERY ETC., - STARTS AT THE TOP AND  DWINDLES DOWN.  I DEFINITELY WILL BE CONTACTING CORPORATE!

I have to say that I have dined at every single potbellys in Washington, DC and many in Maryland and Virginia and this my friends is by far the worst.  The staff sucks, they're rude.  I've been to this location a total of 4 times and 3 out of the 4 times there were verbal altercations between the employees and the patrons. They've gotten my order wrong all 4 times I've been there, it's crazy. They take so long to process the order.  It's really ridiculous, I could understand if they were understaffed but there are 5 people behind the counter and the manager is floating.  National Harbor does it with 4 and it's usually always busy when I go to that location.  The food obviously is the same quality it is good that's the reason why I gave it a 2 star rating instead of a 1 star rating. I would not recommend this location to my worst enemy.  This is truly the black sheep store of the Potbelly franchise.
great service, but I could be biased.

DO NOT GO TO THIS LOCATION - INADEQUATE MANAGMENT  I work at a local business right across the way from this Potbelly. While Potbelly food is delicious and I highly recommend it, DO NOT GO TO THIS LOCATION. We have ordered there multiple times and each time it has been wrong.  This last time was the last time we will order from 1st NE Potbelly. I made an online order through a guest account. I was emailed a confirmation that the order would be ready at 1:30pm and that my order was processed with a credit card online. When I went to pick it up, the incredibly rude sales associate told me that no such order was made. Ok, it could have been an error. I went back to my place of work and made a 2nd order with a newly made account and selected to pay in person after verifying that my card had not been charged - it appeared to have been my error.  When I went to go pick up the 2nd order, I printed out my confirmation...not only was the order not ready at the 2:00pm pick up, they hadn't printed my order and the same rude sales associate had to use my email confirmation to make the order. When it was done, he threw the bags at me and that was it.  Upon returning to work, 1/3 of my order was missing. This has happened before and they delivered the missing items. I called and spoke with the Manager who refused to deliver this missing items, she tried to push for the order charges to be taken off my card. I insisted and she made a delivery time available (an hour later) and then said to me "CHECK YOUR ORDER BEFORE YOU LEAVE". This appalling customer service alone confirmed that we will never order from there again, BUT I received a call later that day that my credit card was never charged...but I had a receipt...IT WAS FOR THE 1ST ORDER that I was so RUDELY told was never placed.

Horrible staff with no care for customers.  Ordered online for delivery with the confirmation and the credit card was charged.  Food was never delivered.  Called the store and they said..... I have to call them to confirm the order.  What a BS.

My order was processed and after an hour the delivery didn't show up. I called them and found out they have a minimum of $25 which is nowhere to be found on the website. When I called, the manager at present told me I NEED to call them for confirmation. What the hell? I already have my email confirmation. BIG THUMBS DOWN for their lack of business sense.
